# SnakeConverter — Global Rules

## Stack
Vanilla JS · Tailwind CSS CDN · HTML5 Canvas · No backend · No build step for dev

## Non-negotiables
- All styles → `css/app.css`. Never add reusable styles in `<style>` blocks.
- All form inputs must have `class="input-field"` — prevents white-on-white text in dark theme.
- Every text element visible to the user needs a `data-i18n="key"` attribute.
- EN + TR translations must always be added together in `js/i18n.js`.
- Never `alert()` — show errors/results in the DOM.

## Before finishing any task
1. Confirm the feature works in the browser (don't just assume).
2. Switch language EN↔TR and verify all text updates.
3. Check browser console — zero errors allowed.

## File ownership (don't cross-pollinate)
- Layout/visual → `css/app.css` + HTML class names
- Tool logic → `js/*.js` namespaces (`CalcTools`, `DevTools`, etc.)
- Translations → `js/i18n.js` + `data-i18n` attributes
- Animation → `js/snake-tools.js` (integration), `js/snake-mascot.js` (engine only)
